Fittsâ€™s law

1 Summary

Fittsâ€™s law states that thereâ€™s a trade-off between speed and accuracy. It is expressed by the formula MT = a + b x ID, where a and b are constants depending on the task and ID is the index of difficulty. ID is determined by the formula ID = log2(A+1/W), where A is the amplitude and W is the width of the target. In this analyse we examine if thereâ€™s a difference between typical and PD speakers when it comes to Fittsâ€™s law. In this analysis, MT is the time2target.

2 List of factors

Factor Description
time2target (MT in Fittsâ€™s law) the time from GONS to MAXC
ID the index of difficulty
pace average number of repetitions per second across the trial
trial.no trial number in the experiment
rep.no repetition number within the trial, ranging from 1 to 10
